Yes — next is Batch 3: 120-storage.

Storage is the section where mistakes get expensive, so I’m separating the simple autopart options from the explicit dynamic partitioning options. Red Hat’s Kickstart docs say autopart should not be mixed with part, raid, logvol, or volgroup; clearpart --all can erase all reachable disks if not limited; ignoredisk --only-use limits what disks the installer can use; and VG/LV names should avoid dashes. That is why these use names like rootvg, datavg, vartmp, and separate the automatic layouts from the generated /tmp/part.conf layouts.  ￼

